I&#x27;m having trouble grokking whatever type-added syntax you&#x27;re using for Javascript here.  I&#x27;m guessing it&#x27;s:<p><pre><code>  function ap(pf) {
    return (pa) =>
      pf.then((f) => pa.then((a) => Promise.resolve(f(a))))
  }
</code></pre>
Still, if I wanted to go full-hog static-typed functional I doubt I&#x27;d be using straight Javascript, I&#x27;d probably try one of the various Haskell-alike to JS converters.  Promises with async/await syntax seems like the most practical of the various solutions whilst still feeling like Javascript.<p>(Besides, I prefer dynamic typing and I find points-free style in Haskell to be obfuscating rather than clarifying, so it seems unlikely we&#x27;re going to have the same opinion of the best way to accomplish things here.  :)
